The paper deals with the problem of active semi-supervised learning on graphs, which is a topic that falls under the broad area of machine learning. The use of graph signals and the graph Laplacian matrix suggests that the paper may be related to graph theory and signal processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Signal Processing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
